Trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}. Halve lengthways then thinly
slice widthways. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and
all). Halve the @red chilli{1/2} lengthways, deseed then slice thinly. Pour the
@water for the stock{750%ml}(for the stock) into a #pan{} and add the
@vegetable stock powder{2}. Pop onto high heat and bring to the boil, then reduce
the heat to low (you want to just keep it warm).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #wide bottomed pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add
the leek and fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir occasionally. Once soft,
stir in the garlic and @tomato puree{30%g} (and a splash more oil if it's a bit
dry). Stir and cook for ~{1%minute}. Add the @Arborio rice{175%g}, stir and cook
for ~{1%minute} until the edges are starting to look translucent. Add the
@cider vinegar{15%ml} and allow it to evaporate, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in a ladle of stock. When the stock has been absorbed by the rice, stir in
another ladle of stock. Keep the pan on medium heat and continue stirring in
stock, letting it absorb each time. The cooking time should be ~{20-25%minutes},
your risotto is done when your rice is 'al dente' - cooked through but with a
tiny bit of firmness left in the middle.

> TIP: You may not need all your stock or you may need a bit of extra water.

When the risotto has 5 mins left, stir in the @king prawns{150%g} and simmer until
they are cooked, ~{5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Once cooked, remove the risotto from the heat and add the
@grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}, a @?butter{1%knob} (if you have some) and
half the parsley. Stir vigorously until the cheese and butter have melted.

Taste the risotto and add @salt{} and @pepper{} if you feel it needs it. Serve the
risotto in #bowls{} with the red chilli (use less chilli if you don't like heat)
and remaining parsley sprinkled on top. Enjoy!